task.summary: Fixed the zipImages() function (now working, but must be manually called (for both zipping and downloading))
Fixed the zipImages() function (now working, but must be manually called (for both zipping and downloading))

-Clicks on "Tools" on GoogleImages when page first loads -Constraint sliders work better -Sliders are not contained in an HTMLTableElement -added toggleEncryptedGoogle -added a replaceThumbWithVid() to replace thumbnails with original videos -added CSS for Google Images constraint sliders + non-qualified images
Created function "setStyleByHTML", you can now force styles by using "!important" Fixed bug where unblocked sites didn't always get colored.

- Created a Tokens object containing className constants - Added the KeyEvent object containing keyCode constants as well as the modKeys object - Fixed .blur.in and .blur.out classNames with CSS selectors - Added cbox_OnlyShowQualifiedImages: a checkbox on the page that only displayed qualified images (WIP) - Changed "window.onkeyup" to "window.addEventListener"

- Collected GM constants and put them all in an object: Constants.GMValues, also collected commonly used selectors in Constants.Selectors - Added text blocks in front of images showing their extensions (png or gif etc..) - Created GSaves class to manage GSaves cards and wrap them with anchors, now it works by accessing the google object directly - The getMeta function now deletes some unnecessary symbols. - Renaming variables: zipImages=>gZipImages, IP=>ImagePanel - Fixed urlArgs injection

- Created and fixed zipImages() - Created setupProgressBar(), script will still work if ProgressBar wasn't included - Fixed an issue with the fileCleaner pattern where not all characters where escaped enough times

- Added Mousetrap library to handle keyBinding and added more shortcuts - Added functions addClass(), setBorder(), to have more centralized control - Changed Google-specific CSS so that the containers will get the borders instead of the images themselves - Can now download images even if not on Google images
Renaming: ddgHandleError -> handleErrorDdg

- Collected GM constants and put them all in an object: Constants.GMValues, also collected commonly used selectors in Constants.Selectors - Added text blocks in front of images showing their extensions (png or gif etc..) - Finalized wrapGSavesPanelsWithAnchors, now it works by accessing the google object directly - Added injectGoogleButtons() from DisplayOriginalImages.user.js - renamed zipImages to gZipImages - Fixed urlArgs injection - Created GetSortedWords() - Added getValidIteratedName() to the zip - Added index.html to zip - Moved zip functions (such as genZip()) to the zip object itself

- Added Mousetrap
- Created class SrcSet Added functions: createAndGetNavbar() fetchDoc() removeClickListeners() iterateOverURLPattern() getElementsWithText() printElementTextAttributes() getIncrementedUrl() freezeGif()

- Added a remote mimeType database and a local JSON string as a backup - Created zipFiles() and zipImages() - Fixed mimeType issues when zipping files, now they will rename the extensions properly - Script will not stop because there is no Progressbar anymore, a null-check has been added

- Added addImgDownloadButton() which appends tiny download buttons to the thumbnails (Also modified some CSS for these buttons) - addImgDownloadButton(), now hovering over a thumbnail for a bit will replace it with the original
Added "RARBG - Add Magnet Link & thumbnails" script and fixed thumbnails not appearing
fixed magnet link button not appearing
